I have y. honour of yo of 18th & 25 past, & sence rec. y. pack of
kersyes arrived with Josua Wilkinson, butt alltogether wet by zea watter
hee haveinge suffered great stormin att zea, where by most his loadinge
is endomaged, god bee thanked, itt is not worse this high ex. & dear
goods, stops mij comissions for y wintter for indeed cottens att such a rate
will heardly returne their cost, my cosen told mee hee shall have some
so I shall helpe him to putt them off, for season goeth farre, & 6
french men of warr are a cousinge before castend, that our convoy
dares not peep out, & lord knowes when y goods now provided
shall bee here: if you can putt of y banck noater, that you shall have
rec for my acco., without yo preiudice, you shall particurareley oblige
mee, & itt shall helpe to y. domage I suffered by y. karsyes, therefore
pray do all what you can, wee are all in hopes of peace this wintter
when there shall bee here a brisgue demande, within a month wee

I have recd. in due time yo of 11. past, & thanke for yo. advice
& whereas my assortem. for winter of northren goods are most for all
bought this time, by y on Kent, so is to late for y turne to
send anney orders y concult iour in trade, & ex. in y reason I have
not writt to you this 2 yeares, butt now I hope all things will
setle, & come into y. old channell, there by that wee shall have peace
this wonther, 0 if succeds shall give occasion of avery good sale
